LOOK.
MY PURSE.

13:49.150 --> 13:52.550
WHAT IS IT?

13:52.550 --> 13:55.220
IT'S A HARD DRIVE.

13:55.220 --> 13:57.690
I WENT IN THE HOUSE
AND TOOK IT.

13:57.690 --> 13:58.890
GOOD.

13:58.890 --> 14:00.490
NOW WE HAVE TO DESTROY IT.

14:00.490 --> 14:02.890
[ SIGHS ]
THANK YOU.

14:02.890 --> 14:05.520
WILL YOU DESTROY HIM
WHILE YOU'RE AT IT?

14:05.520 --> 14:08.420
YOU KNOW, THIS, UH --
THIS ANGER...

14:08.420 --> 14:10.550
IT'S NOT GOOD FOR EITHER
ONE OF US.

14:10.550 --> 14:12.620
I'M JUST NOT READY
TO LET THIS GO YET.

14:12.620 --> 14:14.290
I HAVEN'T WORKED
THROUGH IT.

14:14.290 --> 14:16.420
WELL, YOU HAVE
THE DIVORCE NOW, SO...

14:16.420 --> 14:17.950
MAYBE IT'S TIME
TO MOVE ON.

14:17.950 --> 14:19.550
LOOK,
IT'S NOT THAT EASY.

14:19.550 --> 14:21.150
HE MADE ME
LOSE A BABY, BRAD.

14:21.150 --> 14:22.290
I KNOW.

14:22.290 --> 14:24.150
IT'S EASY
FOR YOU TO MOVE ON.

14:24.150 --> 14:25.420
WELL, HOW CAN YOU
SAY THAT?

14:25.420 --> 14:27.490
I MEAN, I'VE GOT KIDS
WITH THAT WOMAN.

14:27.490 --> 14:29.090
YEAH, BUT YOU STILL HAVE
A LOVE FOR HER.

14:29.090 --> 14:31.550
YOU CAN RATIONALIZE IT.

14:31.550 --> 14:34.020
YEAH, WELL, EVEN LOVE
HAS ITS LIMITS.

14:34.020 --> 14:35.550
I JUST --
I DON'T UNDERSTAND THIS.

14:35.550 --> 14:37.420
I NEVER DID ANYTHING WRONG
TO HIM.

14:37.420 --> 14:38.520
YEAH, I KNOW, I KNOW.

14:38.520 --> 14:40.590
HE STARTED ALL OF THIS.

14:40.590 --> 14:44.990
AND HE'S PROBABLY DEAD SET
ON FINISHING IT, TOO.

14:44.990 --> 14:46.390
I'M NOT GONNA
LET THAT HAPPEN.

14:46.390 --> 14:48.750
MARCIE...

14:48.750 --> 14:52.250
I KNOW YOU KNOW SOMEONE.

14:52.250 --> 14:55.190
WHAT,
I KNOW SOMEONE WHAT?

14:55.190 --> 14:57.520
YOU WERE
IN THE MILITARY.

14:57.520 --> 14:59.790
YOU HAVE TO KNOW SOMEONE.

14:59.790 --> 15:03.320
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

15:03.320 --> 15:04.890
SOMEONE
THAT CAN KILL HIM.

15:08.920 --> 15:10.490
YOU'RE UPSET.

15:10.490 --> 15:12.950
YOU'RE REALLY UPSET.

15:12.950 --> 15:14.220
BUT DON'T TALK ABOUT THAT.

15:14.220 --> 15:16.690
IT'S NOT GOOD.

15:16.690 --> 15:19.490
I KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING.

15:19.490 --> 15:21.020
DON'T.
SERIOUSLY, DON'T.

15:21.020 --> 15:22.090
KELLY DID IT.

15:22.090 --> 15:24.690
AND LOOK
WHERE SHE IS NOW.

15:24.690 --> 15:25.750
IT'S GOTTA BE BETTER
THAN LOOKING

15:25.750 --> 15:27.890
AT HIS DAMN FACE
EVERY DAY.

15:27.890 --> 15:31.220
WELL, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
SEE HIM EVERY DAY.

15:31.220 --> 15:32.950
I JUST WANT HIM TO...

15:32.950 --> 15:34.590
SHH, LOVE, COME ON.

15:36.820 --> 15:38.450
GET ME ANOTHER DAMN DRINK,
PLEASE.

15:41.290 --> 15:42.890
OKAY.

15:45.020 --> 15:46.690
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

15:46.690 --> 15:49.350
WHO IS IT THIS TIME?

15:49.350 --> 15:51.090
IT'S YOUR BOYFRIEND.

15:51.090 --> 15:53.850
HE'S NOT MY BOYFRIEND.

15:53.850 --> 15:54.950
IT'S IAN.

15:54.950 --> 15:57.350
DAMN IT.

15:57.350 --> 16:00.490
OH, CRAP.

16:00.490 --> 16:02.750
I WAS SUPPOSED TO GIVE HIM
HIS KEYS TODAY.

16:02.750 --> 16:03.890
I'M SURE
HE'LL UNDERSTAND.

16:03.890 --> 16:04.890
NO, NO.

16:04.890 --> 16:06.220
DON'T WANT TO SIT
AROUND HERE.

16:06.220 --> 16:07.490
HELLO?

16:07.490 --> 16:08.950
Ian: Hi, Marcie.

16:08.950 --> 16:10.490
HI.

16:10.490 --> 16:12.220
I was trying
to reach you.

16:12.220 --> 16:13.950
YEAH, I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

16:13.950 --> 16:15.250
I, UH, HAD A...

16:15.250 --> 16:17.320
A REALLY BAD SITUATION
COME UP.

16:17.320 --> 16:18.920
Are you okay?

16:18.920 --> 16:21.720
YEAH, YEAH, I'M FINE.

16:21.720 --> 16:23.050
Okay.

16:23.050 --> 16:24.490
You got those keys for me?

16:24.490 --> 16:26.750
YES. YES,
THEY'RE AT THE OFFICE.

16:26.750 --> 16:28.890
UM, I CAN MEET YOU
AT THE HOUSE.

16:28.890 --> 16:30.150
Yes, yes, let's do that.

16:30.150 --> 16:31.950
How about around 6:00
when I get off?

16:31.950 --> 16:33.550
YEAH, SURE,
THAT WOULD WORK.

16:33.550 --> 16:34.750
Okay.

16:34.750 --> 16:36.220
OKAY, THANK YOU.

16:39.690 --> 16:41.490
YOU REALLY
GOING OVER THERE?

16:41.490 --> 16:42.620
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

16:42.620 --> 16:44.020
I GOTTA PAY THE RENT
ON THIS PLACE.

16:44.020 --> 16:45.890
NO, I MEAN, I CAN GO
OVER THERE FOR YOU.

16:45.890 --> 16:47.090
I CAN MEET HIM.

16:47.090 --> 16:49.020
NO.
NO, THAT WOULD BE WEIRD.

16:49.020 --> 16:50.090
HELL, YOU --
WELL, YOU SAID

16:50.090 --> 16:51.490
HE'S BUYING
ON OUR OLD STREET, RIGHT?

16:51.490 --> 16:54.350
I MEAN, I -- SERIOUSLY,
I DON'T MIND, MARCIE.

16:54.350 --> 16:55.620
IT'S FINE, REALLY.

16:55.620 --> 16:56.890
ABOUT THREE MINUTES AGO,

16:56.890 --> 16:58.290
YOU WERE JUST TALKING
ABOUT KILLING RANDAL.

16:58.290 --> 17:00.490
I REALLY DON'T THINK YOU SHOULD
GO ANYWHERE NEAR HIS HOUSE.

17:00.490 --> 17:04.050
YEAH,
THAT HASN'T CHANGED.

17:04.050 --> 17:05.220
I REALLY DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD BE THERE.

17:05.220 --> 17:08.520
I'M FINE, REALLY.
THANK YOU.

17:08.520 --> 17:10.350
OKAY. YOU'RE GONNA DRIVE
AFTER YOU'VE...

17:10.350 --> 17:12.020
MM-HMM.

17:14.320 --> 17:15.720
OKAY.

17:15.720 --> 17:17.120
I'LL BE FINE.

17:17.120 --> 17:19.190
OKAY?

17:19.190 --> 17:20.990
WILL YOU BE HERE
WHEN I GET BACK?

17:20.990 --> 17:23.250
UM...YEAH.

17:23.250 --> 17:26.690
I MEAN,
IF YOU WANT ME TO BE.

17:26.690 --> 17:29.090
I DO.

17:29.090 --> 17:31.890
THEN I WILL.

17:31.890 --> 17:33.220
OKAY.

17:33.220 --> 17:34.550
I'LL TEXT YOU
WHEN I GET THERE

17:34.550 --> 17:35.550
AND LET YOU KNOW, OKAY?

17:35.550 --> 17:38.350
OKAY.

17:38.350 --> 17:39.990
SHOES.

17:43.220 --> 17:44.820
BE RIGHT BACK.
OKAY.

17:44.820 --> 17:53.290
♪♪

17:57.950 --> 18:08.290
♪♪

18:08.290 --> 18:11.390
GET THESE OFF OF ME!

18:11.390 --> 18:13.420
GET THESE OFF OF ME!
UNTIE ME!

18:13.420 --> 18:16.020
I SEE YOU'RE AWAKE.

18:16.020 --> 18:17.590
UNCUFF ME!

18:17.590 --> 18:19.290
SORRY,
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

18:19.290 --> 18:25.490
♪♪

18:25.490 --> 18:27.850
WAIT,
THIS WASN'T A DREAM?

18:27.850 --> 18:29.590
NO.

18:32.420 --> 18:34.420
AND I KILLED HIM?

18:34.420 --> 18:36.020
KILLED WHO?

18:38.950 --> 18:41.790
TRAVIS.

18:41.790 --> 18:43.350
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE YOU ARE?

18:47.250 --> 18:49.390
I'M IN JAIL.

18:49.390 --> 18:51.590
YES.

18:51.590 --> 18:54.150
WELL, WHAT PART
OF THE JAIL?

18:54.150 --> 18:57.490
OBVIOUSLY THE HOSPITAL.

18:57.490 --> 18:58.890
WAIT, BUT...

18:58.890 --> 19:01.420
BUT WHY AM I --
WHY AM I HERE?

19:03.890 --> 19:06.290
YOU DON'T REMEMBER?

19:06.290 --> 19:08.020
NO.

19:08.020 --> 19:09.750
YOU TRIED
TO HURT YOURSELF.

19:12.090 --> 19:13.490
NO, I DIDN'T.
YES, YOU DID.

19:13.490 --> 19:15.220
NO, I DIDN'T.
YES.

19:15.220 --> 19:17.220
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THE DOCTOR'S NOT HERE.

19:17.220 --> 19:19.220
HE'LL BE IN IN A MOMENT,
BUT, IN THE MEANTIME,

19:19.220 --> 19:21.890
I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO TAKE THIS.

19:21.890 --> 19:23.290
WAIT, WHAT'S THAT?

19:23.290 --> 19:25.890
JUST, UH, A LITTLE SOMETHING
TO HELP YOU CALM DOWN.

19:25.890 --> 19:26.990
WAIT, NO --
YOU WILL

19:26.990 --> 19:28.450
OR WE WILL FORCE IT
IN YOUR ARM.

19:28.450 --> 19:30.490
I DON'T WANT TO TAKE THAT.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:30.490 --> 19:31.950
YOU CAN DO THIS THE EASY WAY
OR THE HARD WAY.

19:31.950 --> 19:33.650
NO, GET AWAY FROM --
LUSHION!

19:33.650 --> 19:35.290
LUSHION!
-LUSHION.

19:35.290 --> 19:37.820
EVERYTHING OKAY?

19:37.820 --> 19:39.490
YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.

19:39.490 --> 19:41.220
COME ON, KIM.

19:41.220 --> 19:43.750
GIVE ME A BREAK.

19:43.750 --> 19:45.550
YOU TRYING
TO GET ME FIRED?

19:45.550 --> 19:48.020
NO, NO.

19:48.020 --> 19:49.750
JUST TRYING
TO SEE A FRIEND.

19:54.150 --> 19:56.020
GO AHEAD.

19:56.020 --> 20:00.220
BUT IF THE DOCTOR COMES,
I'M GONNA BLAST YOUR ASS

20:00.220 --> 20:02.150
LIKE I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
YOU WERE HERE.

20:04.790 --> 20:06.490
DEAL.

20:06.490 --> 20:11.690
♪♪

20:11.690 --> 20:13.890
LUSHION...

20:13.890 --> 20:15.620
HEY.

20:15.620 --> 20:18.350
I WANT TO GO HOME.

20:18.350 --> 20:19.550
I KNOW.

20:19.550 --> 20:21.390
CAN I?

20:21.390 --> 20:23.720
NO, YOU CAN'T.

20:23.720 --> 20:26.190
LUSHION,
I CAN'T DO THIS.

20:26.190 --> 20:27.820
YES, YOU CAN.

20:27.820 --> 20:32.950
♪♪

20:32.950 --> 20:35.250
I WANT
TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

20:35.250 --> 20:37.020
WHAT?

20:37.020 --> 20:38.950
LOOK.

20:38.950 --> 20:42.090
NO, GO AHEAD, LOOK.
LOOK.

20:42.090 --> 20:43.690
LOOK AT HIM.
NO, I CAN'T LOOK AT HIM.

20:43.690 --> 20:48.350
LOOK AT HIM, THAT'S ALL
THE REASON YOU NEED TO LIVE.

20:48.350 --> 20:51.090
TRAVIS TOOK EVERYTHING.

20:51.090 --> 20:53.390
AND YOU'RE GONNA GET THAT BACK
AND MORE.

20:53.390 --> 20:54.590
I KNOW YOU'RE
A CHURCH-GOING WOMAN.

20:54.590 --> 20:56.150
YOU KNOW THAT.

20:58.250 --> 21:01.090
LUSHION, I DID IT.

21:01.090 --> 21:02.890
YOU SNAPPED.

21:02.890 --> 21:05.420
I DID IT.

21:05.420 --> 21:08.550
I KILLED HIM.

21:08.550 --> 21:11.950
I CAN'T DEAL WITH THAT.

21:11.950 --> 21:13.550
I CAN'T.

21:13.550 --> 21:15.820
YES, YOU CAN.

21:15.820 --> 21:19.290
NO, NO,
LUSHION, I CAN'T.

21:19.290 --> 21:21.420
WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
WOULD I BE TO JUSTICE?

21:21.420 --> 21:22.750
I CAN'T --
I CAN'T DEAL WITH THIS.

21:22.750 --> 21:24.150
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK, LOOK, LOOK,
I CAN'T DEAL WITH THIS.

21:24.150 --> 21:25.550
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK, LOOK, LOOK,
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK.

21:25.550 --> 21:26.820
PLEASE, JUST GET ME OUT
OF HERE, PLEASE.

21:26.820 --> 21:28.090
HEY, HEY.

21:28.090 --> 21:30.150
PLEASE, LUSHION I CAN'T --
I CAN'T STAY HERE.

21:30.150 --> 21:31.820
LISTEN -- LISTEN TO ME.
I CAN'T STAY HERE, PLEASE.

21:31.820 --> 21:33.750
LISTEN -- WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT. SHH.

21:33.750 --> 21:35.820
PLEASE, LUSHION,
JUST GET ME OUT.

21:35.820 --> 21:37.150
LISTEN, I NEED YOU --
I NEED YOU --

21:37.150 --> 21:39.590
I NEED YOU TO RELAX.
I NEED YOU TO RELAX, OKAY?

21:39.590 --> 21:40.590
JUST RELAX.

21:40.590 --> 21:44.020
RELAX. RELAX.
OKAY?

21:44.020 --> 21:46.020
JUSTICE...

21:46.020 --> 21:48.290
JUSTICE LOVES YOU.

21:48.290 --> 21:49.990
REMEMBER
THAT HE LOVES YOU.

21:52.220 --> 21:53.750
OKAY?

21:53.750 --> 21:55.620
COME ON.
OKAY.

21:57.150 --> 22:01.020
I NEED YOU TO JUST
BREATHE AND RELAX.

22:02.150 --> 22:05.220
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.
LOOK AT ME.

22:05.220 --> 22:06.490
I'M HERE.

22:06.490 --> 22:09.220
I'M RIGHT HERE WITH YOU.

22:09.220 --> 22:12.150
ALRIGHT?

22:12.150 --> 22:16.120
I WANT YOU
TO STAY STRONG, OKAY?

22:16.120 --> 22:17.120
I GOTTA GO.

22:17.120 --> 22:18.750
NO, DON'T.
NO, NO, NO.

22:18.750 --> 22:20.290
PLEASE DON'T LEAVE ME, LUSHION.
IT'S NOT GOOD FOR ME --

22:20.290 --> 22:21.320
PLEASE DON'T LEAVE ME
IN HERE, PLEASE.

22:21.320 --> 22:23.820
IT'S NOT GOOD
FOR ME TO BE HERE.

22:23.820 --> 22:25.950
I NEED TO BE OUT THERE
GETTING YOU SOME HELP.

22:28.290 --> 22:29.890
YOU CAN DO THIS.

22:29.890 --> 22:32.120
[ PANTING ]

22:32.120 --> 22:35.520
NAH, NAH, NAH.
RELAX, RELAX, BREATHE.

22:35.520 --> 22:37.120
OKAY.
OKAY.

22:40.920 --> 22:42.420
OKAY.
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE.

22:42.420 --> 22:44.090
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE.

22:44.090 --> 22:45.950
CAN YOU
COME BACK SOON, PLEASE?

22:45.950 --> 22:47.090
OF COURSE I AM.

22:47.090 --> 22:49.220
PLEASE.

22:49.220 --> 22:50.550
OKAY.

22:50.550 --> 22:52.850
AND I PROMISE YOU,

22:52.850 --> 22:56.850
EDWARD IS NEVER GONNA COME
BY YOUR CELL AGAIN.

22:58.320 --> 22:59.990
EDWARD?

22:59.990 --> 23:01.420
YEAH.

23:01.420 --> 23:04.190
HE SAID HE TALKED TO YOU.

23:04.190 --> 23:07.150
NO, HE DIDN'T.

23:07.150 --> 23:08.490
HE DIDN'T?

23:08.490 --> 23:11.220
NO.

23:11.220 --> 23:13.650
YOU SURE?

23:13.650 --> 23:15.590
YEAH, THAT'S, UH...

23:15.590 --> 23:17.150
THAT'S WHAT HE SAID.

23:20.820 --> 23:23.190
OKAY.

23:23.190 --> 23:25.120
ALRIGHT, ALRIGHT,
YOU JUST, UH...

23:27.650 --> 23:29.450
...RELAX.

23:29.450 --> 23:31.390
OKAY.

23:31.390 --> 23:34.990
ALRIGHT.
I'LL BE BACK.

23:34.990 --> 23:36.350
LUSHION...

23:36.350 --> 23:39.720
OKAY, JUST RE--
JUST RELAX.

23:39.720 --> 23:41.420
OKAY, COME BACK SOON.

23:43.620 --> 23:46.550
I'LL BE BACK.

23:46.550 --> 23:48.290
ALRIGHT.

23:48.290 --> 23:57.150
♪♪

23:57.150 --> 23:58.750
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:05.550 --> 24:06.820
HOW DID YOU FIND OUT?

24:06.820 --> 24:08.290
I WAS WALKING
DOWN THE STREET,

24:08.290 --> 24:10.550
I SAW ALL THESE FIREFIGHTERS
ALL IN SMOKE.

24:10.550 --> 24:12.220
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

24:12.220 --> 24:14.450
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

24:16.420 --> 24:18.690
IT SEEMS PRETTY CALM
OUT HERE.

24:18.690 --> 24:20.150
YEAH, NOW IT DOES.

24:20.150 --> 24:23.020
-HEY.
-HEY.

24:23.020 --> 24:25.020
YOU OKAY?

24:25.020 --> 24:26.750
YEAH.

24:26.750 --> 24:28.290
NATALIE TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED.

24:28.290 --> 24:29.650
YEAH.

24:29.650 --> 24:31.550
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS?

24:31.550 --> 24:33.350
WELL, DO YOU KNOW WHO DID IT?
WHAT...?

24:33.350 --> 24:35.350
NO, I DON'T KNOW.
DID YOU CALL THE COPS?

24:35.350 --> 24:37.490
I MEAN,
IT MAY HAVE BEEN BRAD.

24:37.490 --> 24:39.420
HE'S MAD ENOUGH AT US.

24:39.420 --> 24:40.550
I DIDN'T CALL THEM,

24:40.550 --> 24:42.020
BUT I SAW RANDAL TALKING
TO THEM EARLIER.

24:42.020 --> 24:43.890
YEAH, NO,
I'M SURE HE CALLED.

24:43.890 --> 24:46.220
OKAY, WELL, YEAH.
HE SHOULD HAVE.

24:46.220 --> 24:47.890
THIS IS -- THIS IS SERIOUS.

24:47.890 --> 24:50.150
I MEAN,
MAYBE I DESERVE THIS.

24:50.150 --> 24:51.420
OKAY, STOP.

24:51.420 --> 24:54.950
YOU DO NOT DESERVE
TO BE LOCKED UP IN A SHED.

24:54.950 --> 24:57.350
I'M JUST SAYING,
I-I STARTED ALL OF THIS.

24:57.350 --> 24:58.420
ALEX, STOP.

24:58.420 --> 25:00.750
NO, SHE DID.

25:00.750 --> 25:02.620
ARE YOU TRYING TO MAKE HER
FEEL WORSE?

25:02.620 --> 25:05.550
NO, I'M TRYING TO GET HER
TO DEAL WITH THE TRUTH.

25:05.550 --> 25:06.950
YOU KNOW I DON'T PULL
NO PUNCHES.

25:06.950 --> 25:08.220
YEAH, THAT'S THE PROBLEM
WITH YOU.

25:08.220 --> 25:09.890
GIRL.
NO, IT'S OKAY.

25:09.890 --> 25:11.090
I'M SORRY, ALEX.

25:11.090 --> 25:14.620
IT'S REALLY NOT --
OKAY, WAIT A SECOND.

25:14.620 --> 25:17.890
SO, BRAD WAS MOVING IN?

25:17.890 --> 25:19.090
YEAH.

25:19.090 --> 25:21.350
AND WHY --
NOT ANYMORE.

25:21.350 --> 25:23.620
WHY WERE YOU IN THE SHED?

25:23.620 --> 25:27.220
[ SIGHS ]

25:27.220 --> 25:29.550
'CAUSE I LIED
TO BRAD AGAIN.

25:29.550 --> 25:31.090
AGAIN?
ALEX...

25:31.090 --> 25:33.650
I KNOW, I JUST...

25:33.650 --> 25:35.520
I DON'T KNOW WHY.
I JUST,

25:35.520 --> 25:37.420
I-I DO STUPID THINGS
SOMETIMES.

25:37.420 --> 25:40.950
WHAT DID YOU --
WHAT DID YOU LIE ABOUT?

25:40.950 --> 25:44.750
I TOLD HIM THAT DR. RASTON
SWITCHED THE DNA.

25:44.750 --> 25:46.220
YEAH,
BUT SHE DID, RIGHT?

25:46.220 --> 25:47.690
RIGHT.
SHE DID, NO?

25:47.690 --> 25:49.420
NO.
SHE DIDN'T.

25:49.420 --> 25:50.550
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

25:50.550 --> 25:54.220
SHE DIDN'T. SHE TOLD ME
THAT SHE DIDN'T.

25:54.220 --> 25:56.550
AND WHEN HE ASKED ME,
I COULDN'T BRING MYSELF

25:56.550 --> 25:58.420
TO TELL HIM
THAT SHE DIDN'T,

25:58.420 --> 25:59.820
BECAUSE I DIDN'T
WANT HIM THINKING

25:59.820 --> 26:02.590
THAT I WAS SLEEPING AROUND
WITH OTHER MEN.

26:02.590 --> 26:05.790
ALEX, I'M --
HONEY, YOU GOT TO STOP LYING.

26:05.790 --> 26:07.050
DON'T YOU THINK
I KNOW THAT?!

26:07.050 --> 26:08.450
LOOK, NOW,
DON'T GET MAD AT HER.

26:08.450 --> 26:09.850
I'M NOT MAD AT HER,
I'M -- SORRY.

26:09.850 --> 26:10.850
WAIT A MINUTE.

26:10.850 --> 26:12.550
I'M NOT MAD AT ANYBODY
BUT MYSELF.

26:12.550 --> 26:16.550
OKAY, WAIT A MINUTE,
WHOSE BABY IS IT, THEN?

26:16.550 --> 26:18.820
IT'S RANDAL'S.

26:18.820 --> 26:20.890
I DON'T KNOW,
I DON'T KNOW.

26:20.890 --> 26:22.420
YEAH, BUT THE DNA...

26:22.420 --> 26:24.490
LOOK, I KNOW,
OKAY, I KNOW.

26:24.490 --> 26:25.750
BUT SOMETHING GOT SWITCHED

26:25.750 --> 26:27.720
OR -- OR -- MESSED UP
